  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were, at that time, they did not call-- I think-- that at that time, it was not-- I know that the city became Judenrein at that time, when we left Auschwitz or Oswiecim.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I think they called it more like a resettlement to the city of Sosnowiec.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we-- and life totally changed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were cramped in a one, two room place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] like a-- we were just shoved in in two rooms, which were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] limited-- with limited bathrooms and wash-- and a place where you can wash up.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was-- life changed completely.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And a few weeks later, a few months later, they started to take my older brother, my older sisters to-- to forced labor camps.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So every time [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there was a-- you had to report-- you know, they-- you would be taken to a labor camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] lager, they called it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I know that my parents were-- pulled a lot of strings somehow so that the girls would go to a women's camp, which they did.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They go-- they went to the [INAUDIBLE], and two different camps, by the way, for the-- for my sisters.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE], which was part of Czechoslovakia, that-- but the Germans already occupied it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and they worked in a-- they worked in a-- in a factory sewing uniforms.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were also guarded by women guards at that time.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
